<subSubSection id="12C265757522A07B1EAFFCE2FB466B77" pageId="8" pageNumber="71" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="5A6736FE7522A07B1EAFFCE2FBBF6AE7" blockId="8.[151,1437,834,1435]" pageId="8" pageNumber="71">
<emphasis id="68ACEAEC7522A07B1EAFFCE2FE406D5B" bold="true" box="[151,392,834,859]" pageId="8" pageNumber="71">Material examined.</emphasis>
<materialsCitation id="EAB03CA37522A07B1FAEFCE2FBBF6AE7" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="2147524573" collectingDate="2016-05-31" collectingDateMax="2016-06-17" collectingDateMin="2016-05-31" collectorName="Dostrup Simested A" country="Denmark" location="DENMARK" pageId="8" pageNumber="71" specimenCount="1" typeStatus="holotype">
<typeStatus id="8563885C7522A07B1FAEFCE2FE366D5B" box="[406,510,834,859]" pageId="8" pageNumber="71">Holotype</typeStatus>
male, 
<collectingCountry id="22CF766E7522A07B1C60FCE3FD216D5B" box="[600,745,835,859]" name="Denmark" pageId="8" pageNumber="71">DENMARK</collectingCountry>
, Dk NEJ, 
<collectorName id="F72D53287522A07B1D49FCE3FBAB6D5B" box="[881,1123,834,859]" pageId="8" pageNumber="71">Døstrup Simested Å</collectorName>
, 
<date id="2E66103E7522A07B1ABEFCE2FA8D6D5B" box="[1158,1349,834,859]" pageId="8" pageNumber="71" value="2016-05-31" valueMax="2016-06-17" valueMin="2016-05-31">
<collectingDate id="3E22E9D67522A07B1ABEFCE2FA8D6D5B" box="[1158,1349,834,859]" pageId="8" pageNumber="71" value="2016-05-31" valueMax="2016-06-17" valueMin="2016-05-31">31.v.–17.vi.2016</collectingDate>
</date>
, Esben Bøggild (CUMZ-8-61). Description. Male. Frons as 
<figureCitation id="C2E32A7B7522A07B1CD9FCC6FCFB6D7F" box="[737,819,870,895]" captionStart="FIGURES 54–62" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1976,1999]" captionTargetBox="[273,1290,200,1952]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[261,1326,193,1965]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 54–62. Megaselia helleorumae sp. n. male. 54. left side of frons. 55. postpedicels, palps and proboscis. 56. ventral face of proboscis. 57. abdominal tergites 3–6. 58–59. hypopygium. 60. front tarsus. 61. hind femur. 62. wing." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2617705/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="71">Fig. 54</figureCitation>
, and with dense microtrichia. Cheek with 3 bristles and jowl with 2 that are longer and more robust. Postpedicels, which lack SPS vesicles, palps and proboscis as 
<figureCitation id="C2E32A7B7522A07B1B7EFC2AFA506DA3" box="[1350,1432,906,931]" captionStart="FIGURES 54–62" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1976,1999]" captionTargetBox="[273,1290,200,1952]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[261,1326,193,1965]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 54–62. Megaselia helleorumae sp. n. male. 54. left side of frons. 55. postpedicels, palps and proboscis. 56. ventral face of proboscis. 57. abdominal tergites 3–6. 58–59. hypopygium. 60. front tarsus. 61. hind femur. 62. wing." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2617705/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="71">Fig. 55</figureCitation>
. Ventral face of proboscis as 
<figureCitation id="C2E32A7B7522A07B1FD0FC0EFDF66DC7" box="[488,574,942,967]" captionStart="FIGURES 54–62" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1976,1999]" captionTargetBox="[273,1290,200,1952]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[261,1326,193,1965]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 54–62. Megaselia helleorumae sp. n. male. 54. left side of frons. 55. postpedicels, palps and proboscis. 56. ventral face of proboscis. 57. abdominal tergites 3–6. 58–59. hypopygium. 60. front tarsus. 61. hind femur. 62. wing." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2617705/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="71">Fig. 56</figureCitation>
. Thorax brown, with 2 notopleural bristles and no cleft in front of these. Mesopleuron bare. Scutellum with an anterior pair of small hairs and a posterior pair of bristles. Abdominal tergites 3–6 as 
<figureCitation id="C2E32A7B7522A07B1ED7FC56FE8D6A0F" box="[239,325,1014,1039]" captionStart="FIGURES 54–62" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1976,1999]" captionTargetBox="[273,1290,200,1952]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[261,1326,193,1965]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 54–62. Megaselia helleorumae sp. n. male. 54. left side of frons. 55. postpedicels, palps and proboscis. 56. ventral face of proboscis. 57. abdominal tergites 3–6. 58–59. hypopygium. 60. front tarsus. 61. hind femur. 62. wing." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2617705/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="71">Fig. 57</figureCitation>
. Venter gray, and with hairs on segments 3–6. Hypopygium as 
<figureCitation id="C2E32A7B7522A07B1A0EFC56FB116A0F" box="[1078,1241,1014,1039]" captionStart="FIGURES 54–62" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1976,1999]" captionTargetBox="[273,1290,200,1952]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[261,1326,193,1965]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 54–62. Megaselia helleorumae sp. n. male. 54. left side of frons. 55. postpedicels, palps and proboscis. 56. ventral face of proboscis. 57. abdominal tergites 3–6. 58–59. hypopygium. 60. front tarsus. 61. hind femur. 62. wing." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2617705/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="71">Figs 58 &amp; 59</figureCitation>
, with a pale left hypandrial lobe with microtrichia. The right lobe vestigial but with microtrichia. Legs dusky yellow. Fore tarsus (
<figureCitation id="C2E32A7B7522A07B1EA7FB9EFF396A57" box="[159,241,1086,1111]" captionStart="FIGURES 54–62" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1976,1999]" captionTargetBox="[273,1290,200,1952]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[261,1326,193,1965]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 54–62. Megaselia helleorumae sp. n. male. 54. left side of frons. 55. postpedicels, palps and proboscis. 56. ventral face of proboscis. 57. abdominal tergites 3–6. 58–59. hypopygium. 60. front tarsus. 61. hind femur. 62. wing." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2617705/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="71">Fig. 60</figureCitation>
) with a posterodorsal hair palisade on segments 1–4. Dorsal hair palisade of mid tibia extends about 0.75 times its length. Hind femur as 
<figureCitation id="C2E32A7B7522A07B1C21FBC2FDB96A7B" box="[537,625,1122,1147]" captionStart="FIGURES 54–62" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1976,1999]" captionTargetBox="[273,1290,200,1952]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[261,1326,193,1965]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 54–62. Megaselia helleorumae sp. n. male. 54. left side of frons. 55. postpedicels, palps and proboscis. 56. ventral face of proboscis. 57. abdominal tergites 3–6. 58–59. hypopygium. 60. front tarsus. 61. hind femur. 62. wing." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2617705/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="71">Fig. 61</figureCitation>
. Hind tibia with about 10 differentiated posterodorsal hairs, without anterodorsals, and spinules of apical combs simple. Wings (
<figureCitation id="C2E32A7B7522A07B1D0BFB26FC4C6A9F" box="[819,900,1158,1183]" captionStart="FIGURES 54–62" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1976,1999]" captionTargetBox="[273,1290,200,1952]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[261,1326,193,1965]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 54–62. Megaselia helleorumae sp. n. male. 54. left side of frons. 55. postpedicels, palps and proboscis. 56. ventral face of proboscis. 57. abdominal tergites 3–6. 58–59. hypopygium. 60. front tarsus. 61. hind femur. 62. wing." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2617705/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="71">Fig. 62</figureCitation>
) 
<quantity id="9D209B1B7522A07B1DABFB27FC3F6A9E" box="[915,1015,1159,1183]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.01" pageId="8" pageNumber="71" unit="mm" value="2.01">2.01 mm</quantity>
long. Costal index 0.45. Costal ratios 4.06: 2.11: 1. Costal cilia (of section 3) 
<quantity id="9D209B1B7522A07B1C58FB0BFD0C6AC2" box="[608,708,1195,1219]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" pageId="8" pageNumber="71" unit="mm" value="0.12">0.12 mm</quantity>
long. Vein 3 with hair at base of 
<quantity id="9D209B1B7522A07B1A0EFB0BFB526AC2" box="[1078,1178,1195,1219]" metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="8" pageNumber="71" unit="mm" value="0.04">0.04 mm</quantity>
length. With 4 axillary bristles, the outermost being 
<quantity id="9D209B1B7522A07B1FE3FB6EFDB66AE6" box="[475,638,1230,1255]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.45" metricValueMax="1.5" metricValueMin="1.4" pageId="8" pageNumber="71" unit="mm" value="0.145" valueMax="0.15" valueMin="0.14">0.14–0.15 mm</quantity>
long. Sc not reaching R1. Haltere knob pale.
</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5A6736FE7522A07B1EFFFB52FB466B77" blockId="8.[151,1437,834,1435]" pageId="8" pageNumber="71">
<emphasis id="68ACEAEC7522A07B1EFFFB52FE956B0B" bold="true" box="[199,349,1266,1291]" pageId="8" pageNumber="71">Recognition.</emphasis>
In the key of 
<bibRefCitation id="3E494B0F7522A07B1FC2FB52FD746B0B" author="Lundbeck, W." box="[506,700,1266,1291]" pageId="8" pageNumber="71" refId="ref7421" refString="Lundbeck, W. (1922) Diptera Danica. Part UI. Pipunculidae, Phoridae. Wesley, London, 455 pp." type="book" year="1922">Lundbeck (1922)</bibRefCitation>
to Group 
<mcCollectionCode id="8FF553717522A07B1D16FB53FC836B0A" box="[814,843,1267,1290]" country="Norway" name="Mykotektet, National Veterinary Institute" pageId="8" pageNumber="71">VI</mcCollectionCode>
it runs to couplet 31 where neither option fits. In the key to the males of the British species (
<bibRefCitation id="3E494B0F7522A07B1C5AFAB6FD346B2F" author="Disney, R. H. L." box="[610,764,1302,1327]" pageId="8" pageNumber="71" pagination="1 - 155" refId="ref7235" refString="Disney, R. H. L. (1989) Scuttle Flies-Diptera Phoridae Genus Megaselia. Handbooks for the Identification of British Insects, 10 (8), 1 - 155." type="journal article" year="1989">Disney, 1989</bibRefCitation>
) it runs to triplet 218, but its hypopygium differs from all three species. A further nine species will run to the same triplet, but all differ in their hypopygia plus one or more characters, e.g. vein 3 unforked, notopleuron with a cleft, popstpedicels with SPS vesicles.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="12C265757522A07B1EFFFA22FBCE6B9B" box="[199,1030,1410,1435]" pageId="8" pageNumber="71" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="5A6736FE7522A07B1EFFFA22FBCE6B9B" blockId="8.[151,1437,834,1435]" box="[199,1030,1410,1435]" pageId="8" pageNumber="71">
<emphasis id="68ACEAEC7522A07B1EFFFA22FE806B9B" bold="true" box="[199,328,1410,1435]" pageId="8" pageNumber="71">Etymology</emphasis>
. Named after Helle Ørum a close colleague of Esben Bøggild.
</paragraph>
